import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of S&P 500 index prices over the years?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    sns.boxplot(x='price', data=data)
    median_price = data['price'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_price, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_price:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average daily closing price of the S&P 500 index?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['moving_average'] = data['price'].rolling(window=20).mean()
    
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data, label='Price')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='moving_average', data=data, label='Moving Average')
    
    plt.title('What is the volatility of the S&P 500 index prices?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
